            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Transhumanism, Moore's Law, etc..."><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Transhumanism, Moore's Law, etc...<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~aristofanes" class="author" title="author name and user ID">aristofanes (413195) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3660149&cid=43486143">(#43486143)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43486143" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>In 1954 Norbert Wiener published "The Human Use of Human Beings: Cybernetics and Society.<br>In it he said:"...let us remember that automatic machines, whatever we think of any feelings it may have or may not have is the precise economic equivalent of slave labor. Any labor which competes with slave labor must accept the economic conditions of slave labor"(p.220)</p><p>Is there any good answer to this forecast?</p></div>
